activities:
Sony Pictures Entertainment Inc. will use and otherwise process EU Employee Data in the United States for the following purposes: 
 
•	Personnel administration; 
•	Travel and expense reimbursement; 
•	Compensation related activities, including stock plan administration and compensation and bonus analysis and administration; 
•	Job grading and recruitment activities;
•	Payroll processing;
•	Performance management;
•	Compliance with legal and regulatory requirements;
•	Monitoring and enforcing compliance with company policies and procedures;
•	Providing IT support and services; and
•	Finance and accounting related activities.   
As necessary in connection with these purposes, the Human Resources department and company managers, as well as members of the IT department on a limited basis, in the United States may access and otherwise process EU Employee Data in connection with their job responsibilities.  Sony Pictures Entertainment Inc. takes appropriate steps to ensure that such personnel are bound by duties of confidentiality with respect to EU Employee Data.

Sony Pictures Entertainment Inc. may also use and otherwise process EU corporate customer and supplier personal information in the United States for purposes of carrying out transactions and performing related finance and accounting activities, and for other legitimate business and compliance activities.
